Determine the output of the following code:

```java
int result = 0;
for (int i = 1; i <= 4; i++) {
    result += i * 2;
}
System.out.println(result);
```

Determine the output of the following code:

```java
for (int i = 10; i >= 1; i -= 3) {
    System.out.print(i + " ");
}
```

Determine the values of `a` and `b` after the following code runs:

```java
int a = 1;
int b = 0;
for (int i = 1; i <= 5; i++) {
    b = a + b;
    a = b - a;
}
```

Consider the following `for` loop:

```java
for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
    System.out.println(i);
}
```

Which of the following `while` loops is equivalent?

options.text:
```java
int i = 0;
while (i < n) {
    i++;
    System.out.println(i);
}
```

```java
int i = 0;
while (i < n) {
    System.out.println(i);
    i++;
}
```

```java
int i = 0;
while (!(i < n)) {
    System.out.println(i);
    i++;
}
```

```java
int i = 0;
i++;
while (i < n) {
    System.out.println(i);
    i++;
}
```

